Follow these instructions to ensure the application runs correctly.

Pre-requisites: 
Download and install the lastest .NET-Connector from www.mysql.com
Access to MySql connection
Visual Studio

STEP 1
________________
Create a new Windows Form App (.NET Framework) in Visual Studio

STEP2
________________
Add the MySQL.Data in Visual Studio to your project references (Menu: project --> [application name] Properties --> References).

STEP 3
________________
Create a total of 8 application settings (Salespeople, Product, Client, CSVFile, DBName, DBUsername, DBPassword, ServerName) 
of type "string", scope "user" with empty value fields.

STEP 4
________________
Create 5 forms in Visual Studio and copy and paste the code 
